WEBVTT

01:19.906 --> 01:20.527
Good morning.

01:22.229 --> 01:40.151
It is a joy to be with you this morning, and even though today, it's a joy to be with you this morning, but I think most of us know if you are a member of Concorde, unless you're watching online today, if you're one of the campuses or here, most of us know today is not a normal Sunday at Concorde Baptist Church.

01:40.171 --> 01:48.722
We are, this is the first Sunday for all of us, myself included, sort of a post Levi Sunday, and I just wanted to before I launch into the message today,

01:49.026 --> 01:53.674
acknowledge that that being the case it's a day that's filled with emotions of all different kinds.

01:54.255 --> 02:05.796
I've heard all different kinds of responses from folks as you know we've all processed the fact that Levi's called to a greater opportunity and he's now working as the head of evangelism for the Georgia Baptist Mission Board.

02:07.319 --> 02:13.650
Some of the folks I've talked with have said you know that is just their their response to that first and foremost has just been excitement

02:13.922 --> 02:18.147
And thankfulness that God has called Levi to a greater platform.

02:18.167 --> 02:20.590
He'll have an opportunity to influence an entire state.

02:21.091 --> 02:22.252
And I am thankful for that.

02:22.713 --> 02:23.794
And thank God for that.

02:23.894 --> 02:28.459
And proud to have been a part, as Concord, proud to have been a part of preparing him for that.

02:29.320 --> 02:36.830
But I'd be lying if I told you that my first response was to be excited and proud when Levi told me that he was going to be going to a different place.

02:36.850 --> 02:38.752
I don't know what your first response was.

02:38.932 --> 02:40.594
Don't know what your response is right now.

02:41.314 --> 02:50.684
Now, today is the day I would imagine that some folks who are sad, and I can understand that, some folks may be who are angry or may be anxious.

02:51.485 --> 02:57.512
Now, those are just all ways that normal human beings process change and loss, and so it is okay.

02:58.233 --> 03:06.802
Whatever you feel today, I'm not trying to tell you how to feel about it, but I just want to acknowledge this is not a normal day at Concord, but I think it is a great day.

03:08.098 --> 03:11.382
We're all processing a change that we may not have expected.

03:11.443 --> 03:15.368
What happens for churches as a whole also happens for individuals.

03:16.890 --> 03:19.553
As a church, we may be at that spot where we say, you know, what now?

03:19.994 --> 03:20.575
What next?

03:21.837 --> 03:29.026
But individuals get to that same spot from time to time where life throws you a curve, something you did not expect.

03:30.268 --> 03:34.834
Maybe there's a change you have to process or a loss that you have to deal with.

03:34.978 --> 03:37.341
You're not sure how you're going to deal with that thing.

03:37.361 --> 03:40.005
It may be that it's exciting, a new opportunity.

03:40.065 --> 03:42.067
It may be that it's ominous and threatening.

03:42.107 --> 03:43.830
But in any case, it's different.

03:44.791 --> 03:46.613
And you're not sure what to do with that.

03:46.653 --> 03:48.235
So you're asking that same question.

03:48.296 --> 03:49.337
What now?

03:50.599 --> 03:51.119
What next?

03:52.821 --> 03:56.046
Whenever you get to that spot and you're asking that question, what now?

03:56.126 --> 03:56.647
What next?

03:56.667 --> 04:02.354
You're in a season of life where it's as if somebody's turning the page or moving to a different chapter.

04:03.010 --> 04:16.890
I think there are always some things that we can stop and focus on that are going to help us in knowing how we're going to manage that transition, how we're going to live effectively in that next season, whether it's true for a whole church or it's true for you and me as individuals.

04:17.071 --> 04:23.120
And so because of that, I want to, for the next several weeks, I want to talk to you about the subject of focus.

04:24.362 --> 04:30.130
Because when we're managing a change, it's always vital what we decide to focus on.

04:30.978 --> 04:36.684
If we focus on the right things and we can manage that change effectively, come out of it stronger and better than ever before.

04:37.906 --> 04:40.328
If we don't focus, then sometimes we begin to drift.

04:40.408 --> 04:45.394
We begin to lose our way and just kind of make sometimes make bad decisions, wrong decisions.

04:45.414 --> 04:48.117
I hope that's not going to be a case for any of us here.

04:49.318 --> 04:52.762
For Concord, I think this issue of focus is a vital one for us.

04:54.424 --> 04:56.306
You know, my primary emotion

04:56.674 --> 05:01.720
personally for the change that we're going through is really one of thankfulness in the sense that I'm thankful.

05:03.002 --> 05:09.350
I'm so thankful for the good and wise leader that God gave us for the last nine years.

05:10.691 --> 05:13.375
I'm thankful that God has expanded our borders.

05:13.415 --> 05:20.203
We're a larger church and that's one way, but I'm thankful and a more meaningful sense that God has enlarged our vision.

05:22.185 --> 05:25.970
When I compare where Concord is today to where we were nine years ago,

05:26.146 --> 05:32.675
I know that we understand it a greater way than ever before, what our potential is and what can take place through the ministry of this church.

05:33.997 --> 05:35.059
And we don't need to lose that.

05:36.020 --> 05:37.342
We don't need to lose energy.

05:37.382 --> 05:38.644
We don't need to lose momentum.

05:38.684 --> 05:39.645
I don't think we have to.

05:40.126 --> 05:42.950
As long as we focus, we can maintain that momentum.

05:42.970 --> 05:44.772
And I think come out stronger than ever before.

05:47.136 --> 05:47.977
That's true for churches.

05:48.057 --> 05:48.818
It's true for people.

05:49.960 --> 05:54.386
The passage you want to look at way to this morning as we move into this series as a passage,

05:54.498 --> 05:57.683
from the book of Hebrews and the 12th chapter, the first couple of verses.

05:59.185 --> 06:03.852
It talks about how we deal with drift or the temptation to drift in a season of change.

06:04.834 --> 06:10.422
And it is written by a writer who is telling the folks in his day and time.

06:10.883 --> 06:12.626
These are normal folks like you and me.

06:12.666 --> 06:23.122
They're folks who are dealing with all kinds of changes that life brings, many of which may have been unexpected, some of which may have been obstacles or challenges or even fears.

06:23.682 --> 06:29.468
But if you read the 11th chapter of the book of Hebrews, it just goes right before this passage we'll look at today.

06:29.788 --> 06:33.872
What you'll find there is almost a kind of a who's who of the Old Testament.

06:34.873 --> 06:45.224
Person after person who faced obstacles and challenges, fears of all types, but who overcame their obstacles and their challenges to live effectively.

06:45.845 --> 06:48.147
So much so that we're still talking about them today.

06:49.649 --> 06:51.090
And the writer of Hebrews is

06:51.330 --> 07:02.743
It's as if he says, I want you to imagine that great cloud of witnesses, all these people who have already run their ricks and lived effectively overcome their challenges.

07:02.823 --> 07:10.872
And now it's as if he says, it's as if they're peering over the boundaries of heaven and they're watching us and they're asking that question, what now?

07:12.754 --> 07:14.676
And what are these people gonna do now?

07:14.716 --> 07:19.922
Whether we talk about us as a whole, as Concord or talk about you individually, the challenges that you face.

07:20.930 --> 07:29.664
And as he asks them to imagine this scenario, it's as if the writer is saying to the people in his day and time, I want you to focus.

07:30.726 --> 07:32.609
And here's how you can focus.

07:32.809 --> 07:35.454
Here are some of the places that you need to focus.

07:35.514 --> 07:39.781
If you want to live well and live effectively, given the realities of your day and time.

07:41.023 --> 07:41.804
So here's the text.

07:42.725 --> 07:46.792
And in honor of God's word, as we always do, let's all stand together and let's read it together.

07:46.832 --> 07:48.114
Hebrews chapter 12,

07:48.322 --> 07:51.867
The first couple of verses I'm reading from the New American Standard Bible.

07:52.689 --> 08:05.829
The Bible says, therefore, since we have so great a cloud of witnesses surrounding us, let us also, like they did, lay aside every encumbrance your Bible may say, wait.

08:07.792 --> 08:12.319
And the sin which so easily entangles us and let us run like they did.

08:13.841 --> 08:16.786
With endurance, the race that is set before us,

08:17.474 --> 08:31.133
fixing our eyes on Jesus, the author and perfecter of our faith, who for the joy set before Him endured the cross, despising the shame, and sat down at the right hand of the throne of God.

08:32.715 --> 08:33.436
Thank you.

08:33.456 --> 08:36.701
You can be seated.

08:36.721 --> 08:40.306
So how do we live effectively?

08:41.378 --> 08:52.329
in the midst of changes that we may not have expected, in midst of challenges or obstacles and sometimes fears, whatever you're facing today, how do we live effectively in real life?

08:53.971 --> 09:08.146
The writer of Hebrew says to the people that he, his audience, the folks that he wanted to encourage, he says, there are just a few things I want you to remember, and the first of those things is you live effectively when you remember what your race is.

09:09.218 --> 09:17.165
Therefore, since we have so great a cloud of witnesses surrounding us, let us also lay aside every encumbrance and let us run with endurance, what?

09:17.546 --> 09:21.610
The race the Bible says that is set before us.

09:24.452 --> 09:25.353
It's a key to life.

09:25.413 --> 09:34.742
You and I today, and we live in the part of the state where if we choose to, I mean, when we get in our car, we can ride past any number of pastures and places where they're all kind of cattle out there.

09:35.162 --> 09:39.186
You probably can't get home today without seeing someplace where they're a cattle in a field.

09:39.426 --> 09:44.193
And if you look over at those cattle today, you'll notice they're chewing their cut or whatever it is that cows do.

09:44.694 --> 09:52.085
And they are completely satisfied to be able to do that today to eat and to sleep and whatever else it is that cows do.

09:52.486 --> 09:55.029
And they're completely satisfied to do that today.

09:55.330 --> 09:59.015
And I'm telling you, they're gonna be completely satisfied to do that tomorrow.

10:00.157 --> 10:06.066
And the day after that, and the day after that, that's just how cows are wired.

10:06.338 --> 10:11.071
Not that I've ever been a cow, mind you, but it's just how they're wired.

10:12.094 --> 10:14.360
They don't have a race to run.

10:14.400 --> 10:22.322
Now, can we all agree this morning that there's a difference between how God wears a cow and how God wears you and me?

10:23.522 --> 10:27.165
You may be in a season of life where you say to yourself, you know, I'm just as tired as I can be.

10:27.226 --> 10:30.148
I would like to live like a cow for just a little while.

10:30.168 --> 10:31.950
I'd like to not have any responsibilities.

10:32.310 --> 10:38.356
I would like just to be able to eat and sleep and do what I want, have no deadlines, no requirements, no worries.

10:39.978 --> 10:43.982
And you can probably do that for just about a week.

10:44.002 --> 10:46.684
And some of you go on vacation, maybe you can do it for two weeks.

10:48.566 --> 10:52.850
But if you're like me at the end of those two weeks, you're looking at your wife, you're saying, I'm ready to go home.

10:55.042 --> 10:59.267
I've held out just about enough of this life where there is no purpose or there's no race to run.

10:59.287 --> 11:01.629
There's no objective to accomplish.

11:03.912 --> 11:12.722
I don't know about you, but if someone pins me not inside of a pasture, maybe they pin me inside of a room and they just feed me and give me what I need to exist, but I can't carry out any purpose.

11:12.762 --> 11:15.745
That's not a, that's not an effective way to live in my mind.

11:19.069 --> 11:20.210
I don't think it is yours either.

11:22.402 --> 11:30.470
The truth is that God has given every one of us a purpose to live for, or in the biblical terms, a race to run.

11:30.490 --> 11:32.452
I don't know what your race is.

11:33.953 --> 11:37.937
Your race is different than mine because you are wired differently than me.

11:37.957 --> 11:39.538
You have different gifts than me.

11:39.578 --> 11:41.400
We all do, and thank God for that.

11:43.342 --> 11:45.164
But every one of us has a race to run.

11:45.204 --> 11:51.730
The guys who lead us in worship this morning, I'm gonna guess that it probably

11:51.842 --> 11:53.484
you know, for Philip or for Joe.

11:53.504 --> 12:01.733
I mean, these are guys who, the opportunity to lead people to the throne of God is not just something, it's a casual endeavor to them.

12:03.395 --> 12:06.999
It's like a fire that burns deep inside of them, something they have to do.

12:09.102 --> 12:11.925
And when they get a chance to do it, there's a joy that's attached to that.

12:12.025 --> 12:14.388
It touches eternity.

12:14.408 --> 12:15.489
They have a race to run.

12:16.570 --> 12:19.954
But Jamie stood here a minute ago and talked to us about vacation Bible school.

12:20.546 --> 12:30.205
That's just one small slice of a ministry that takes place all year long, where people like him and other folks who don't get paid for it, but have tremendous joy in it.

12:30.545 --> 12:33.832
They invest in the lives of people who are the next generation.

12:33.872 --> 12:40.966
And they understand that in being able to do this, that it adds value to their own life, that they have a race to run.

12:41.026 --> 12:43.250
You may be a mom.

12:44.002 --> 12:49.531
And you understand that the deepest purpose you have in this world is to prepare those kids for the next generation.

12:49.791 --> 12:50.993
It's your race to run.

12:52.956 --> 12:58.044
Can I just say to you that nobody lives life effectively if they forget what their race is?

12:59.826 --> 13:07.278
That the right way or the way to live your life effectively in any season is to remember what your race is.

13:11.204 --> 13:12.466
All of us attempted to forget it.

13:14.146 --> 13:18.670
When I think about this subject, the person that comes to my mind most is a lady, and many of you would not know her.

13:18.710 --> 13:20.993
She's with the Lord now.

13:21.033 --> 13:22.234
Her name was Margaret Birx.

13:22.294 --> 13:22.894
Margaret died.

13:22.934 --> 13:24.516
She was just about 100 years old.

13:24.596 --> 13:25.777
She died several years ago.

13:25.817 --> 13:28.199
She was a member of First Baptist Church in Flowery Branch.

13:28.219 --> 13:35.266
And when Margaret was 78 years old, her husband passed.

13:37.228 --> 13:40.711
And she thought, like a lot of people would think, that most of my life is done by now.

13:40.731 --> 13:43.474
I don't have any particular purpose to achieve.

13:43.586 --> 13:55.237
And it was like she was praying one day and she said, you know, if she heard the Lord say to her that he wanted her to go at 78, that he wanted her to go to seminary and study for the ministry.

13:55.257 --> 13:57.019
And she looked to you to tell this story.

13:57.079 --> 13:59.742
She looked up at the Lord and she'd say, Lord, do you know how old I am?

13:59.802 --> 14:03.385
And she'd say, yeah, the Lord said, yes, I know how old you are, I made you.

14:04.326 --> 14:05.467
So she lost that argument.

14:06.328 --> 14:08.310
And at 78, Margaret went to seminary.

14:09.511 --> 14:12.274
In her 80s, Margaret began to go to the mission field.

14:14.306 --> 14:16.888
Can I tell you, I have never seen anybody more alive.

14:19.951 --> 14:23.274
Into her 90s, Margaret got sick in her 90s, late in her 90s.

14:23.315 --> 14:24.836
She couldn't go to the mission field anymore.

14:25.717 --> 14:26.658
And she said, you know what?

14:26.698 --> 14:28.640
My mission field now is a dialysis room.

14:28.660 --> 14:31.402
She would have to be hooked up there all day, all hours at a time.

14:31.442 --> 14:32.383
And the nurses had to stay.

14:32.403 --> 14:33.744
They said, this is my mission field.

14:34.165 --> 14:36.147
She never forgot she had a race to run.

14:38.048 --> 14:39.870
Margaret was a force to be reckoned with.

14:39.910 --> 14:43.954
She was a joy to be around, even until she died.

14:46.882 --> 14:49.385
And she was, every day she lived, fully alive.

14:51.808 --> 14:54.572
Because she never forgot she had a race to run.

14:57.976 --> 15:00.860
Can I just tell you this morning, God has given you a race to run.

15:04.104 --> 15:05.826
It's not my place to tell you what it is.

15:05.987 --> 15:11.854
I can only tell you that the race God has given you to run is a place where your life intersects eternity.

15:13.997 --> 15:14.898
And it matters.

15:16.034 --> 15:17.416
It matters absolutely.

15:18.057 --> 15:21.001
It's what fuels and brings energy to life.

15:22.703 --> 15:25.166
And the way to live effectively is always to remember it.

15:26.848 --> 15:29.272
It's not just true for you and me as an individual.

15:29.332 --> 15:31.975
It's true for all of us as Concord Baptist Church.

15:34.719 --> 15:42.089
My job as the director of missions for the Chattahoochee Baptist Association gives me the privilege of working with churches of all types, all sizes.

15:42.149 --> 15:43.090
I love everyone.

15:44.418 --> 15:46.782
But can I tell you this morning that not all of them are healthy?

15:49.827 --> 15:53.693
And that when they become unhealthy, it's always about this same thing.

15:53.733 --> 16:03.589
That somewhere, somebody, some begins to substitute a different thing as the priority.

16:04.370 --> 16:09.298
A different thing in the place of the race that God has given them to run.

16:10.978 --> 16:20.727
And so now then the priority becomes, you know, whatever makes me comfortable, or maybe the priority becomes, you know, the heritage of something in the past, or you name it.

16:22.629 --> 16:31.397
One of the great joys that we have experienced here at Concord in the last nine years is that our pastor made it so much more plain to us what our race is.

16:31.778 --> 16:35.061
And we all know it, just three words.

16:37.303 --> 16:40.786
Say it with me, making disciples

16:41.058 --> 16:41.739
everywhere.

16:44.161 --> 16:52.829
And if I could give you one word today, just one word I would ask you with me to embrace that race.

16:53.871 --> 17:02.559
Because the truth is, while it may be that we have a different pastor a year from now, six months from now, that those things are changing, that this is not changing.

17:04.541 --> 17:09.746
The race that God has given us, or look at it in the text, the race that is set before us,

17:10.978 --> 17:14.502
is not a race that was set before us by any single pastor.

17:16.604 --> 17:21.089
The race it is set before us was set before us by Jesus himself.

17:21.570 --> 17:32.202
Go ye therefore and make disciples of all the nations, baptizing them and then with the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit, teaching them to observe all things whatsoever I've commanded you.

17:32.422 --> 17:39.730
There's so many churches today that somewhere along the way have decided they're not going to take that race seriously.

17:40.162 --> 17:46.129
And for every time they do, the energy drains out of them and the life drains out of them.

17:46.169 --> 17:56.361
One of the reasons it's been such a joy to be a part of Concord in the last nine years is that our pastor helped us understand our race.

17:56.681 --> 17:57.622
He didn't give it to us.

17:59.605 --> 18:00.626
He just helped us to see it.

18:02.909 --> 18:04.050
And we don't need to forget it.

18:06.594 --> 18:10.900
So if I could say one thing to you, I would say, let's be Concord Baptist Church.

18:11.600 --> 18:15.265
Let's take that race with absolute seriousness.

18:16.727 --> 18:17.829
Let's take it seriously.

18:18.149 --> 18:22.655
And one other thing I want to ask you to do, take it personally.

18:25.198 --> 18:26.420
Because it's not Levi's race.

18:27.361 --> 18:28.562
It's not the staff's race.

18:28.622 --> 18:30.445
It was given to all of us by Jesus.

18:30.505 --> 18:34.450
And it has a personal implication for every one of us.

18:35.746 --> 18:38.569
Remember your race.

18:38.589 --> 18:43.414
Now, if we're going to take it personally, we're going to have to do some things personally to be able to run it.

18:44.895 --> 19:00.512
So in the next part of this text, I would say you and I need to understand that from time to time, it's important that we, if we're going to run this race and run it well, we're going to live effectively with the obstacles, challenges, whatever it is you're facing, then from time to time, we have to declutter our own lives.

19:00.632 --> 19:02.834
Nobody can do this for us.

19:04.770 --> 19:17.007
And if you go to my house today and you go upstairs into the office that I don't supposedly use, though I don't use it much because the truth is the desk in that office is always cluttered with junk.

19:17.728 --> 19:18.770
Anybody here like this?

19:18.950 --> 19:20.312
Anybody here can testify?

19:20.853 --> 19:22.014
Okay, we got a few folks like this.

19:22.835 --> 19:24.738
And it's not that I ever try to clutter it up.

19:24.758 --> 19:28.583
It's just that there's stuff that happens and I'm always thinking, well, I'll take care of that later.

19:28.644 --> 19:30.386
And so if you go up there right now and there's

19:30.498 --> 19:33.901
paper stacked all over the place and you can't even clear off a spot to work.

19:33.941 --> 19:47.855
If you were to go in there to do anything in my office, you would stand there about 15 seconds and roll your eyes and you would turn around and you would leave because you cannot work effectively unless from time to time you get rid of some things.

19:49.796 --> 19:53.320
That's not just true for the desk in my office, it's true for my life as well.

19:54.521 --> 19:59.826
And so the writer of Hebrew says there are a couple of different ways you and I need to, if we want to live effectively,

20:01.026 --> 20:01.406
Focus.

20:03.328 --> 20:07.832
If we're going to live effectively, there are a couple of ways we need to declutter our lives.

20:07.993 --> 20:14.158
And the first is, he says, we need to lay aside things that are wrong.

20:17.121 --> 20:27.151
Let us also lay aside every encumbrance and the sin, he says, that so easily entangles us, things that are wrong.

20:28.632 --> 20:30.834
Now, there's nobody in the room here this morning.

20:32.514 --> 20:37.279
That gets up in the morning on any particular day and says, what can I do today that will entangle my life?

20:40.163 --> 20:41.164
Nobody gets up in the morning.

20:41.184 --> 20:41.965
Let's have a list of things.

20:42.085 --> 20:44.668
What are the most evil things that I can do today?

20:44.708 --> 20:45.769
Nobody does that.

20:45.829 --> 20:55.460
Our lives get entangled when we allow something to attach to us that doesn't belong, something that dishonors God, but we tell ourselves that it's not going to entangle us.

20:55.880 --> 20:57.682
We say, well, it's just a small thing.

20:57.922 --> 21:01.406
It's not a, it's not, nobody even has to know about it.

21:01.426 --> 21:20.087
It's not a big, you know, we make excuses of every variety because somewhere in our minds, we tell ourselves that this sin, whatever it may be, a relationship that doesn't belong, or an attitude that doesn't belong, or a bitterness that doesn't belong, whatever it is, we tell ourselves that it's not gonna entangle us.

21:21.789 --> 21:26.194
Well, the truth is, all we gotta do is look at the news and watch the latest sports star,

21:26.722 --> 21:45.047
the latest movie star, the latest politician whose lust or pride or greed has now destroyed their reputation and tangled their life so that they cannot accomplish what it is that they've been given to do in this world.

21:48.391 --> 21:50.354
The last thing that you want to do

21:51.458 --> 22:09.137
But see, take place in your life to see your potential, your opportunity to run a race that has eternal consequence, to change the lives of the people around you, your children, the people who are in your extended family, the people you teach, the folks you work with, the last thing you want to do is to see your influence destroyed.

22:12.421 --> 22:13.442
And it doesn't have to be.

22:15.644 --> 22:21.010
As long as you and I from time to time will stop and take stock and say, you know, there's some things today that I need to lay aside.

22:24.546 --> 22:28.410
Maybe today what you need to do is to say, you know, I'm going to lay this aside.

22:28.430 --> 22:30.112
I'm going to take it to the Lord.

22:30.132 --> 22:33.015
I'm going to tell somebody else about it so they can hold me accountable about it.

22:33.035 --> 22:34.557
I'm going to become serious about this.

22:36.459 --> 22:41.044
I just want to encourage you to get free today because God's given you a race to run.

22:42.826 --> 22:46.971
And all you need to do to be able to protect that future race is to lay aside some things.

22:47.011 --> 22:48.753
You lay aside some things that are wrong.

22:48.773 --> 22:53.618
You also got to lay aside some things that are not wrong.

22:55.170 --> 22:56.251
but they're just wrong for you.

22:57.833 --> 23:01.498
Or maybe I should say they're wrong for now, for this season.

23:03.220 --> 23:05.082
If you're gonna run the race, God's given you to run.

23:06.444 --> 23:11.871
So what the writer says when he says, let us also lay aside every, here's this word, encumbrance.

23:12.952 --> 23:13.633
It's not a sin.

23:15.896 --> 23:17.578
Your Bible may say, wait.

23:18.659 --> 23:19.921
Lay aside every weight.

23:19.941 --> 23:20.602
It's not a sin.

23:20.662 --> 23:24.146
It's just something that holds you back.

23:26.690 --> 23:29.294
You know, Debbie and I just, I mentioned vacations a while ago.

23:29.315 --> 23:33.442
Debbie and I just got back from vacation Friday, I guess it was.

23:33.662 --> 23:44.380
And I told the first service, everybody needs to, after the service today, you need to come up and reward Deb or shake hands with her, hug her, tell her she's doing a great job.

23:44.421 --> 23:49.369
And she just achieved one of the greatest things in life the other day on vacation.

23:49.409 --> 23:52.274
Because when we went on vacation, I was buying the plane tickets to go.

23:52.962 --> 23:54.845
And I'm like the cheapest person in America.

23:55.245 --> 23:57.249
And so I got on expedient.

23:57.309 --> 23:58.490
I got the best deal.

23:58.651 --> 24:00.514
And I didn't know this till afterwards.

24:00.574 --> 24:05.802
But whatever deal I got was a deal where you couldn't even carry a carry-on bag on.

24:06.002 --> 24:07.865
I mean, they put us in no joke.

24:08.105 --> 24:10.429
They put us, we had two flights on Friday.

24:10.469 --> 24:13.634
They put us in the last seat of the plane, both times.

24:13.894 --> 24:16.278
We couldn't even have a carry-on, you know, luggage.

24:16.718 --> 24:19.122
And so all you could have was what they called a personal item.

24:19.490 --> 24:25.339
So we went over to Belks and we bought these two little suitcases that were like supposed to be under the seat types.

24:25.499 --> 24:27.762
You can't use them in the overhead bin.

24:28.363 --> 24:32.289
And my wife packed for five whole days in California.

24:32.349 --> 24:38.218
And this little thing that was no bigger than this, you guys do not know what an awesome miracle this is.

24:38.278 --> 24:40.221
I'm telling you.

24:41.082 --> 24:47.952
If I were to give you the context, I'd tell you, but when we were first married and we went on vacation the first time, some of you husbands can relate to this.

24:48.272 --> 24:49.394
You know what I'm talking about.

24:50.018 --> 24:54.042
I went inside the house and I packed my bag and it was about like that, you know, a little bag.

24:54.062 --> 24:55.264
I pride myself on this.

24:55.304 --> 24:58.147
So I bring it out and put it down a little two-seater car that we had.

24:58.167 --> 24:59.528
Deb says, I'm ready.

24:59.748 --> 25:05.134
And she comes out and she's pulling out this bag and then this other bag and it's like it's got like a two-two train, man.

25:05.174 --> 25:06.135
It's coming out of the house.

25:06.776 --> 25:10.280
And I'm shoving it all in this little hatchback that we got.

25:10.360 --> 25:15.065
And finally, I get it all in there and I take the lid, the abzod inside the car and I slam it.

25:15.706 --> 25:16.266
Bam!

25:17.027 --> 25:18.048
But as hard as I can.

25:18.689 --> 25:19.730
And I get in the seat.

25:19.874 --> 25:21.356
And I'm as mad as I can be.

25:21.376 --> 25:24.401
And I didn't talk for the first hour and a half of our vacation.

25:26.043 --> 25:27.025
And some of y'all have been there.

25:29.168 --> 25:34.777
And I've got to confess, I have learned that I'm not right.

25:36.299 --> 25:36.940
You heard me say it?

25:38.823 --> 25:39.524
I'm not right.

25:39.564 --> 25:40.345
She's not wrong.

25:41.887 --> 25:45.353
There's nothing righteous about packing a small bag going vacation.

25:45.373 --> 25:48.978
Nothing wrong about packing 15 bags to go on vacation.

25:49.154 --> 25:58.255
As long as you've got a big enough car and as long as you're going on vacation.

25:58.275 --> 26:01.382
But you cannot do that if you're running a race.

26:06.273 --> 26:06.674
You hear me?

26:09.154 --> 26:17.646
If you're running a race, you cannot go down to the peach tree, Julian, July 4th, and drag all that stuff along behind you and live and run that race effectively.

26:17.666 --> 26:20.250
You cannot do that if you're running a race.

26:20.290 --> 26:22.573
It's not a matter of whether it's wrong or right.

26:22.593 --> 26:24.696
It's a matter of whether it's wrong for you.

26:24.756 --> 26:31.566
Now, there may be folks who can take 10 weeks and weekends and go off and do all that kind of stuff, and that's great.

26:31.586 --> 26:32.407
There's nothing wrong with that.

26:32.447 --> 26:34.610
I'm just telling you, it may be wrong for you.

26:35.202 --> 26:47.621
If God's given you a race to run and it involves your being here to teach young people or to invest in the lives of children, listen, it's not that it's wrong or right's wrong for you.

26:48.062 --> 26:49.825
You cannot get in the way for you.

26:51.788 --> 26:53.050
God's given you a race to run.

26:53.090 --> 26:58.338
Nothing is more important than pushing everything out of the way so that you can run it.

27:02.545 --> 27:03.506
Declutter your life.

27:04.898 --> 27:07.221
Remember that God's given you a race to run.

27:07.922 --> 27:09.323
Nothing matters more than this.

27:09.784 --> 27:10.945
Lay aside what's wrong.

27:11.947 --> 27:13.649
That threatens your ability to run that race.

27:13.669 --> 27:15.130
Lay aside what's wrong for you.

27:16.752 --> 27:19.295
You know at Concord, there's certain things we don't do here.

27:20.457 --> 27:22.059
You may have been at a different church sometime.

27:22.079 --> 27:24.201
They did a ministry there that was a great ministry.

27:25.263 --> 27:26.184
No complaints for that.

27:26.244 --> 27:29.287
But listen, if you come and say, hey, let's do this or let's do.

27:29.688 --> 27:31.410
Concord can't do everything.

27:33.154 --> 27:36.578
Because God has called us and we understand that God has called us to do something.

27:38.701 --> 27:40.263
Make disciples everywhere.

27:42.265 --> 27:51.096
Every dollar we spend, every action we take, every ministry we carry out has to directly connect to that one thing.

27:51.517 --> 27:53.259
Make disciples everywhere.

27:54.560 --> 27:56.122
It's the race God has given us to run.

27:58.946 --> 27:59.607
Remember your race.

28:02.009 --> 28:02.450
Today,

28:02.850 --> 28:28.585
Declutter your life declutter streamline it focused Do what God's called you to do and learn how to reenergize constantly This is a skill not everybody has But it's a skill that you and I have to learn how to to do well.

28:28.605 --> 28:29.106
We have to

28:29.730 --> 28:34.035
The Bible says we run with endurance fixing our eyes on Jesus.

28:35.436 --> 28:36.798
And you see that word, endurance.

28:39.521 --> 28:40.822
And I was never a great athlete.

28:42.324 --> 28:44.946
If you go, I ran track and I ran cross country in high school.

28:44.966 --> 28:50.272
But if you go to look at the record books or the state of Georgia, you won't find my name anyplace on any record anywhere.

28:50.773 --> 28:52.374
Because I was never all that great at it.

28:53.376 --> 28:55.698
But I do know what it's like to run a race.

28:58.018 --> 29:02.486
And let me tell you, I never ran a race that was not exhausting.

29:03.668 --> 29:10.680
I don't care if it was a sprint or a mile or a marathon, I never, you guys know what I'm talking about?

29:12.664 --> 29:17.072
There's no such thing as a race that isn't tiring.

29:20.398 --> 29:22.802
And when you run the race that God has given you to run,

29:24.482 --> 29:27.765
You shouldn't expect that it will not from time to time be exhausting.

29:27.845 --> 29:30.408
It may be from time to time excruciating.

29:30.428 --> 29:31.169
That's appropriate.

29:31.189 --> 29:33.651
That's what racists are like.

29:33.671 --> 29:40.178
And so you and I have to understand how do we, in the midst of that reality, how do we constantly re-energize?

29:40.258 --> 29:45.263
And the writer of Hebrews tells his audience, here's how you focus.

29:46.084 --> 29:47.525
Here's how you live effectively.

29:47.545 --> 29:50.408
You learn to fix your eyes on the right place.

29:50.468 --> 29:52.530
It's all about how we focus.

29:54.210 --> 29:57.615
fixing your eyes, he says, on Jesus.

30:00.139 --> 30:06.829
It's probably worthwhile for us this morning to spend a few minutes saying what this is not telling us to do.

30:08.311 --> 30:21.310
Because there's so many temptations when we get tired or when we are exhausted and we are distracted because of that and then maybe diverted off course, we drift off course, we may stay there for years.

30:23.173 --> 30:23.954
If we don't learn

30:24.514 --> 30:28.139
how to re-energize.

30:28.159 --> 30:32.805
The baubles not say that we are supposed to fix when we are tired our eyes on other people.

30:37.632 --> 30:48.166
Now think about that passage in the last part of John's gospel where Jesus looks at Peter and he says, you know, when you were young, you used to gird yourself and go wherever you wanted to go.

30:50.169 --> 30:51.090
But when you're old,

30:51.746 --> 30:54.550
Someone else will gird you and take you where you don't want to go.

30:56.993 --> 30:59.858
And that's not particularly the race Peter wanted to be able to run.

30:59.878 --> 31:03.663
And so he begins to look around and he sees John over there and he says, what about him?

31:03.703 --> 31:07.048
And Jesus says, if I want him to remain until I come, what is that to you?

31:08.550 --> 31:09.211
You follow me.

31:12.115 --> 31:14.198
And we're all tempted to do that same thing.

31:14.238 --> 31:17.843
We have a race to run that is difficult, it's exhausting sometimes.

31:17.883 --> 31:19.826
And we say, well, what about him?

31:19.938 --> 31:23.163
He doesn't have the financial challenges that I have to deal with.

31:23.704 --> 31:24.525
What about her?

31:24.585 --> 31:28.351
She doesn't have an invalid parent to take care of like I do.

31:28.451 --> 31:29.453
What about that person?

31:29.553 --> 31:31.216
They don't have the health issues I have.

31:31.436 --> 31:32.578
What about this person over here?

31:32.598 --> 31:35.142
It's like their life is always, it seems like, just perfect.

31:35.202 --> 31:39.249
It's like, let me just say to you, you cannot draw energy from that.

31:41.292 --> 31:44.056
That does not add energy to anybody's life.

31:44.116 --> 31:45.338
All it does is subtract.

31:45.358 --> 31:47.762
You cannot fix your eyes on other people.

31:49.186 --> 31:52.470
You can't fix your eyes on how big the problems are.

31:52.891 --> 31:53.732
Some people do that.

31:54.933 --> 31:57.096
And here are the spies going into the Promised Land.

31:57.116 --> 31:59.719
Moses sends these 12 spies into the Promised Land.

31:59.739 --> 32:01.982
They come back with a story about how big the problems are.

32:02.002 --> 32:03.925
It's like, man, it's a huge challenge.

32:03.945 --> 32:04.866
Nobody could do this.

32:04.926 --> 32:09.111
It's like you cannot draw energy from looking at how big the problems are.

32:11.634 --> 32:14.418
You can't draw energy from looking at how small you are.

32:16.994 --> 32:18.035
How limited you are.

32:18.075 --> 32:20.558
It's not about how small I am or limited I am.

32:20.578 --> 32:21.639
It's how big God is.

32:26.684 --> 32:31.929
You can't draw energy from looking at who the preacher is or isn't.

32:37.655 --> 32:45.202
You know, folks, if you're at one of our campuses today and you want to come over to the Claremont campus and go over to what they call the chapel,

32:46.626 --> 32:52.954
There's a stained glass window over there that's got all the names of every pastor who's ever served in this church.

32:53.014 --> 33:00.284
God brings them, God moves them on, but you know what the truth is?

33:02.867 --> 33:11.058
The power that has driven Concord Baptist Church in every generation and every season is Jesus Christ Himself.

33:15.138 --> 33:17.541
the one that every one of those pastors looked to.

33:17.581 --> 33:19.924
You can go beyond that if you want to and get in the graveyard.

33:20.525 --> 33:22.327
There's a whole great cloud of witnesses there.

33:22.567 --> 33:27.974
They had obstacles and challenges of every type and every one of those people learned that they drew strength.

33:27.994 --> 33:34.623
They're not from looking at other people or looking at themselves, but they drew strength from fixing their eyes on Jesus because he is able.

33:35.183 --> 33:40.530
And can I say to you this morning, he is as able as he has ever been for any of those generations.

33:41.410 --> 33:51.580
Can I say to you today that he is as worthy as he has ever been for you and me to give him our very best?

33:53.522 --> 34:10.738
Therefore, since we are surrounded by so great a cloud of witnesses, let us also, like they did, lay aside every weight, every encumbrance, and ascend it so easily entangles us and let us run with endurance, the race,

34:10.978 --> 34:13.841
that is set before us.

34:13.861 --> 34:14.822
Because let me tell you something.

34:16.144 --> 34:20.088
God has given Concord Baptist Church a great race to run.

34:20.128 --> 34:22.130
And we are all a part of it.

34:23.091 --> 34:26.415
I thank God for how He has prepared the day to bring us to this moment.

34:27.136 --> 34:29.358
And I thank God for what He has for us in the future.

34:30.620 --> 34:36.406
And for you and I as we focus, we remember what that race is and we lay aside anything and everything that gets in the way.

34:36.746 --> 34:40.050
And we fix our eyes on one person and one person only.

34:41.282 --> 34:42.544
Jesus Christ Himself.

34:45.289 --> 34:47.233
God has great things in store for Concord.

34:50.179 --> 34:54.687
And as you follow this same pattern in your individual life, God has great things in store for you.

34:57.913 --> 34:59.596
Can I ask you to bow your heads and close your eyes?

35:02.802 --> 35:04.946
In just a minute, we're going to have a hymn of invitation.

35:06.818 --> 35:25.901
Our instrument is gonna come and play, and I just wanna ask if you wanna come today, you may be that you wanna come today and pray for Concord Baptist Church, because you know we're at a new season, a different season, and we need the leadership of Jesus, but let me tell ya, he's as faithful as he's ever been, and that leadership be available to us.

35:27.322 --> 35:33.970
If you wanna come and pray for Concord, I invite you to come, you wanna come and pray for yourself, because you've got a race to run, you maybe have been diverted from that.

35:35.106 --> 35:37.089
You need to recommit to your race this morning.

35:38.911 --> 35:43.617
Maybe you need to come and join this church or trust Christ to be your Lord and Savior this morning.

35:43.957 --> 35:44.438
I want to pray.

35:44.478 --> 35:46.781
And after that, if you'll all stand, we'll have a hymn of invitation.

35:46.861 --> 35:49.785
Father, thank you for the truth of your word.

35:50.165 --> 36:01.800
Thank you that people just like us in every season and every generation, every nation, every part of the world have always been able to run the race you've given them by fixing their eyes on you.

36:02.061 --> 36:03.122
Help us do the same.

36:04.162 --> 36:06.290
We pray in Jesus' name, amen.

